reason.tex:
%text
For f(x) to be continuous at $x=3$,
we know that the following must hold

%
\begin{align}
\underbrace{3\alpha + 1}_{\lim_{x\to 3^-}f(x)} 
&= \underbrace{3\beta + 3}_{\lim_{x\to 3^+}f(x)} 
= \underbrace{3\alpha + 1}_{f(3)} \\ 
\implies 3\alpha + 1 &= 3\beta + 3 \\
\therefore \alpha - \beta &= \frac{2}{3}
\end{align}
